{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17523607","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17523607"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T14:57:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T14:57:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13911"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"13911","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/13911"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.2,0.23,0.43,0.06,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"6530"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112159"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"6530","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/6530"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13911"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94224"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"5"},{"type":"tags","id":"30"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"73"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"627"},{"type":"tags","id":"1139"},{"type":"tags","id":"1643"},{"type":"tags","id":"2436"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"13064"},{"type":"contributions","id":"13065"},{"type":"contributions","id":"14507"},{"type":"contributions","id":"34534"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45973"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"112159","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/112159"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 35-year-old woman presents to the General Practice clinic with a six-month history of weight gain, fatigue, and easy bruising. She has no significant medical history and her only medication is the oral contraceptive pill. On examination, she appears cushingoid with central obesity, moon facies, and abdominal striae. Her vital signs are within normal limits. As part of the investigation for suspected Cushing\u0027s syndrome, a CT scan of the abdomen is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis for the lesion seen in the CT?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Hepatocellular carcinoma","Metastasis","Haemangioma","Liver abscess","Hydatid cyst"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":[],"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EWhilst this patient is being investigated for suspected Cushing\u0027s syndrome, the CT scan has found what is almost certainly an incidental finding in the right lobe of the liver (Image 1). The most likely diagnosis for this incidental lesion is a \u003Cstrong\u003Ehaemangioma\u003C/strong\u003E. Haemangiomas are the most common benign liver lesions, often found incidentally on imaging studies performed for unrelated reasons. They typically appear on contrast-enhanced CT as well-defined lesions with peripheral nodular enhancement in the arterial phase, followed by progressive centripetal fill-in in the portal venous and delayed phases. They typically do not require treatment unless causing symptoms or complications.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHepatocellular carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E (HCC) is less likely in this case. HCC typically occurs in the setting of chronic liver disease or cirrhosis; this is not mentioned in this patient\u0027s history, and there are no signs of macronodular cirrhosis in her CT. Additionally, the imaging characteristics of HCC differ from those of haemangiomas, often with a heterogenous appearance and usually showing arterial phase hyperenhancement followed by washout in the portal venous and delayed phases (Image 2).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELiver abscess\u003C/strong\u003E is an infection of the liver parenchyma that can appear as a hypodense lesion with peripheral enhancement on CT. This typically has a necrotic and low density appearance on imaging with irregular margins, may have internal gas (Image 3) and can be multifocal, none of which is present in the patient\u0027s CT. Liver abscesses are also usually associated with symptoms such as fever, right upper quadrant pain, and elevated inflammatory markers, which are not present in this case.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMetastasis\u003C/strong\u003E should be considered, especially as Cushing syndrome may be caused by a cortisol-secreting adrenal adenoma or adenocarcinoma. However, liver metastases often appear as multiple, heterogeneous lesions with variable enhancement patterns (Image 4).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EHydatid cyst\u003C/strong\u003E is a parasitic infection caused by \u003Cem\u003EEchinococcus granulosus.\u003C/em\u003E On CT, hydatid cysts typically appear as well-defined, hypodense lesions with a thick wall and internal septations or daughter cysts. They also frequently demonstrate calcification (Image 5). The enhancement pattern and appearance in this case is not typical for a hydatid cyst.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Incidental findings on imaging studies are relatively common, being found in at least 25% of abdominal CT scans.","Haemangiomas are the most common benign liver lesions, often found incidentally on imaging studies."],"references":["Klotz T, Montoriol PF, Da Ines D, Petitcolin V, Joubert-Zakeyh J, Garcier JM. Hepatic haemangioma: common and uncommon imaging features. Diagn Interv Imaging. 2013 Sep;94(9):849-59. Available at: https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/23796395/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"94224"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"13911"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"20846"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"21879"},{"type":"media","id":"21880"},{"type":"media","id":"21881"},{"type":"media","id":"21882"},{"type":"media","id":"21883"}]}}},{"type":"media","id":"20846","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/20846"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/BpWTOFHwOmy9Zl1taOfLXdjqi7Wb8M.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/BpWTOFHwOmy9Zl1taOfLXdjqi7Wb8M.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":1208}},{"type":"media","id":"21879","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21879"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5CXc4STBa4702bAQturSBwijldpVbA.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/5CXc4STBa4702bAQturSBwijldpVbA.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1500,"height":1208}},{"type":"media","id":"21880","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21880"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/xeHmHMsZyPYXjxzftD0lnfghdYuROL.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/xeHmHMsZyPYXjxzftD0lnfghdYuROL.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":587,"height":422}},{"type":"media","id":"21881","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21881"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/DcrEpgesqU6ALnoNlgyYgOaPmGqZKQ.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/DcrEpgesqU6ALnoNlgyYgOaPmGqZKQ.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":1213,"height":840}},{"type":"media","id":"21882","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21882"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/wyBEDAxxtUVp3hQ7FdzcmL27O06oOK.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/wyBEDAxxtUVp3hQ7FdzcmL27O06oOK.jpg","isProcessed":true,"width":549,"height":440}},{"type":"media","id":"21883","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/21883"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/pPNwr0OF2HOEgzBEQ38UrfY5hhp8mj.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/stor